hopobject.body: What do you do? force factor test x180 alpha Even though NASA expected its astronauts to not urinate, another government agency did. Engineers at the CIA that were involved with the U-2 spy plane project created an external urine collection device (UCD) back in 1955. Like its name implies, the UCD collects urine and transports it to an external compartment. Even though both the CIA and NASA are government agencies, the UCD technology was not shared between the two.
